5 (3) the creation of a governing committee, and a recommended
6 composition of this committee, that would:
7 (A) administer the fund;
8 (B) develop the benefit package and eligibility thresholds based on
9 capacity to carry out activities of daily living and cognitive challenges; and
10 (C) develop regulations regarding the portability of benefits for
11 persons who pay into the system and then leave Vermont;
12 (4) the viability of persons being eligible for benefits after paying into
13 the program for at least two years; and
14 (5) the transfer of fund resources to Medicaid, to be used in providing
15 long-term care services.
16 (b) The Secretary may receive assistance from any agency, department,
17 division, or office and any board or commission of any such entity, or any
18 independent board or commission, in the Executive Branch of the State.
19 (c) On or before January 15, 2026, the Secretary shall submit a written
20 report on its findings to the House Committees on Appropriations, on Human
21 Services, and on Ways and Means and the Senate Committees on
